From ac4bb9c001f751b58821c9fcbdac9c61c07c8745 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?G=CE=9BB?= <Gab@CosmoLabs.org>
Date: Thu, 30 Apr 2026 16:22:03 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] feat(runner): add setup/teardown lifecycle hooks

Add lifecycle hooks that extend the existing prerequisites mechanism:
- before_all: run once before all tests
- after_all: run once after all tests (with always_run flag for guaranteed execution)
- before_each: run before every test
- after_each: run after every test
- env_pass: capture KEY=VALUE pairs from hook stdout for environment passing

The implementation follows the existing prereq.go patterns and integrates
cleanly with the runner's sequential and parallel execution modes.

Files added:
- internal/runner/lifecycle.go: core hook execution logic
- internal/runner/lifecycle_test.go: unit tests for hook execution
- internal/runner/lifecycle_integration_test.go: end-to-end integration tests
- internal/schema/lifecycle_validate_test.go: validation tests

Files modified:
- internal/schema/schema.go: add LifecycleConfig and LifecycleHook structs
- internal/schema/validate.go: add lifecycle hook validation
- internal/runner/runner.go: integrate lifecycle hooks into test execution

All existing tests pass. 15 new lifecycle unit tests and 7 validation tests added.
